{
  "page": "Jalabhar Xho",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Prince</span><br />Jalabhar Xho</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Felicia_Cano_Jhalabar_Xho.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Felicia Cano Jhalabar Xho.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4b/Felicia_Cano_Jhalabar_Xho.jpg/350px-Felicia_Cano_Jhalabar_Xho.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"292\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4b/Felicia_Cano_Jhalabar_Xho.jpg/525px-Felicia_Cano_Jhalabar_Xho.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/4b/Felicia_Cano_Jhalabar_Xho.jpg/700px-Felicia_Cano_Jhalabar_Xho.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Jalabhar Xho by Felicia Cano © Fantasy Flight Games</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Prince\" title=\"Prince\">Prince</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Flower_Vale\" title=\"Red Flower Vale\">Red Flower Vale</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Xho\" title=\"House Xho\">House Xho</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Islands\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Summer Islands\">Summer Islander</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nthe <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Isles</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Jalabhar Xho</b>, Prince of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Flower_Vale\" title=\"Red Flower Vale\">Red Flower Vale</a>, is an exiled prince from the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Isles</a> residing in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">A Feast for Crows</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Jalabhar_Xho\" title=\"Category:Images of Jalabhar Xho\">Images of Jalabhar Xho</a></div>\n<p>Jalabhar has the dark skin and extravagant feather cape typical of <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Islanders</a>. The feathers of his own cape are green and scarlet.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Jalabhar speaks both the <a href=\"/index.php/Common_Tongue\" title=\"Common Tongue\">Common Tongue</a> and his native <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Tongue\" title=\"Summer Tongue\">Summer Tongue</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> considers Jalabhar to be little more than a highborn beggar,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a> thinks that Jalabhar is seen as an amusing curiosity by the court of King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Jalabhar Xho is the exiled Prince of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Flower_Vale\" title=\"Red Flower Vale\">Red Flower Vale</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> likely exiled for losing a highly ritualized war as per the tradition of the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Isles</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_summer_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_summer_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Following his exile, Jalabhar came to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> to request <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> and swords from King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a> to help him regain the Red Flower Vale. Robert always entertained the notion of conquering the Summer Isles, but always put off Jalabhar's request for help. However, Robert never firmly declined him, telling him \"Next year\" instead of \"No\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While Jalabhar continues to occasionally petition the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> to win back his seat,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> he has become a noted courtier at King's Landing. Having no other place to seek refuge,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> the exiled prince is one of the most colorful figures at court, alongside <a href=\"/index.php/Thoros_of_Myr\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thoros of Myr\">Thoros of Myr</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jalabhar_Xho_by_Amok.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5e/Jalabhar_Xho_by_Amok.jpg/350px-Jalabhar_Xho_by_Amok.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"538\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5e/Jalabhar_Xho_by_Amok.jpg/525px-Jalabhar_Xho_by_Amok.jpg 1.5x, /images/5/5e/Jalabhar_Xho_by_Amok.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jalabhar_Xho_by_Amok.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Jalabhar Xho, by Roman Papsuev ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Jalabhar attends the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand%27s_tourney\" title=\"Hand&#39;s tourney\">Hand's tourney</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Poole\" title=\"Jeyne Poole\">Jeyne Poole</a> admits to <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> that she is frightened by his looks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In the final round of the archery competition, Jalabhar and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Swann\" title=\"Balon Swann\">Balon Swann</a> get outshot by the commoner <a href=\"/index.php/Anguy\" title=\"Anguy\">Anguy</a> at a hundred paces.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the death of King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>, Jalabhar is among the score of nobles who attend King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_I_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Joffrey I Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a>'s first court session in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Jalabhar attends the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_on_King_Joffrey%27s_name_day\" title=\"Tourney on King Joffrey&#39;s name day\">tourney on King Joffrey's name day</a> in King's Landing, one of the few nobles to do so as the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a> has broken out.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The prince is part of the procession that sees Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Myrcella_Baratheon\" title=\"Myrcella Baratheon\">Myrcella Baratheon</a> off to <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>. While returning to the Red Keep, the group is attacked by <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Riots_in_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Riots in King&#39;s Landing\">a riot</a> breaks out in King's Landing. After the group narrowly returns to safety, Jalabhar believes he saw Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Preston_Greenfield\" title=\"Preston Greenfield\">Preston Greenfield</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> ride back to futilely aid the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a>, though he was not certain.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following the defeat of <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, Jalabhar dresses splendidly in feathers for the following court session.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> remembers Jalabhar as the most colorful figure at court, alongside the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priest</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Thoros_of_Myr\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thoros of Myr\">Thoros of Myr</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jalabhar attends <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Tyrion_Lannister_and_Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Wedding of Tyrion Lannister and Sansa Stark\">the wedding</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>. After the ceremony, Jalabhar dances with <a href=\"/index.php/Meredyth_Crane\" title=\"Meredyth Crane\">Meredyth Crane</a>, looking gorgeous in his feathered finery. He also dances with Sansa, telling her something in the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Tongue\" title=\"Summer Tongue\">Summer Tongue</a> that she does not understand.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>As part of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>'s orders, Jalabhar is part of the group that accompanies Tyrion to meet the delegation from <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, ensuring the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a> is greeted by more notables aside from Tyrion. Instead of <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>, however, the the delegation is led by <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jalabhar is a guest at <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_Wedding\" title=\"Purple Wedding\">the wedding</a> of King Joffrey and Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>, gifting Joffrey a great bow of <a href=\"/index.php/Goldenheart\" title=\"Goldenheart\">golden wood</a> and a quiver of arrows fletched with green and scarlet feathers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> After the ceremony, Jalabhar is among the nobles enjoying the unseasonable heat in the courtyard, where Sansa asks him about wedding customs in the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Isles</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\">A Feast for Crows</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/69/Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg/350px-Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"486\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/69/Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg/525px-Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/69/Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg/700px-Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jalabhar_Xho_and_Margaery_Tyrell_by_Amuelia.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Jalabhar Xho and <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>, with her cousins <a href=\"/index.php/Megga_Tyrell\" title=\"Megga Tyrell\">Megga</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Alla_Tyrell\" title=\"Alla Tyrell\">Alla</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Elinor_Tyrell\" title=\"Elinor Tyrell\">Elinor</a>. By Amuelia ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Jalabhar visits Queen Margaery often, teaching her and her handmaids the Summer Tongue,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and attaches himself to her entourage.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> He petitions the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> for aid in retaking his seat, the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Flower_Vale\" title=\"Red Flower Vale\">Red Flower Vale</a>, but is put off by Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Blue_Bard\" title=\"Blue Bard\">Blue Bard</a> is <a href=\"/index.php/Torture\" title=\"Torture\">tortured</a> and forced to list those he claims to have been Queen Margaery's secret lovers, with Jalabhar among them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> Cersei has an arrest warrant signed for Jalabhar as part of her plans to remove Margaery, as well as getting rid of the prince, whom she deems to be an annoying beggar.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Jalabhar is held with the rest of Margaery's falsely-accused lovers in a dungeon, under the charge of <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_21-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Jalabhar Xho was all in feathers, a plumage so fantastic and extravagant that he seemed like to take flight.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote> \n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Beneath his jewels and feathers, Xho was little more than a wellborn beggar. <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert</a> could have put an end to his importuning for good with one firm \"No,\" but the notion of conquering the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Isles</a> had appealed to her drunken lout of a husband.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Splendid as he looked in his bright feather cloak, he had only come to beg.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jalabhar_Xho&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a